description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Homecare Medicines Contract Officer to join our Pharmacy Homecare Team within the Pharmacy Department at University Hospitals Bristol and Weston (Based in Bristol).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will see you supporting our Homecare patients through a variety of duties within the department, involving the processing of prescriptions, orders and invoices. You will be required to liaise with clinical teams, homecare providers and patients to resolve queries and to ensure delivery of medication in a timely manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also be involved interpreting data to support the ongoing contract management of homecare providers and our outsourced outpatient pharmacy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual who is able to manage their own workload; is helpful and approachable; organised and can work accurately. Good IT, problem solving and communication skills are essential&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;PLEASE NOTE: should we have a high volume of applications we may close the vacancy early&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elizabeth Mander, Homecare Contract Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;elizabeth.mander@uhbw.nhs.uk 0117 342 3573&lt;/p&gt;
